step_data.thought:
Looking at the current state of the page, I can see we're back at the URL Rewrites listing page. There's a success message that says 'The URL Rewrite has been saved.' This confirms that our URL rewrite for SEO optimization has been successfully created and saved.

I can see the newly created URL rewrite in the list of URL rewrites. It appears at the top of the list with ID 769, showing:
- Store View: Main Website > Main Website Store > Default Store View
- Request Path: seo-friendly-category
- Target Path: catalog/category/view/id/5
- Redirect Type: Permanent (301)

This means we have successfully configured a URL rewrite for SEO optimization. The rewrite will redirect users from the SEO-friendly URL 'seo-friendly-category' to the internal Magento path 'catalog/category/view/id/5' with a permanent 301 redirect, which is optimal for SEO purposes.

Since we've completed the goal of configuring a URL rewrite for SEO optimization, I should inform the user of the successful completion.
